author: dkulp
msg: Pom cleanups, pipe connection, inProcess cleanups, installer jdk version
* Change installer to build with target 1.4 so 1.4 can be used to install celtix, but gives a warning about requiring 1.5 to run.
* Cleanup poms to move "inherit" more from parent pom and override with just property settings
* Make filtering easier by adding a src/main/resources-filtered optional directory for filtered stuff
* Add ability to ServerLauncher to specify whether it should launch in process or not

* Create "pipe" protocol (protocol, not a transport) for the http transport to pipe to in-process servers.  Bypasses network stack making it easier to profile.  Also about 15% faster for inprocess stuff.
